# z Skill — Handoff Entrypoint: plan-to-work

This session was started via `CONTINUE_SESSION` with `forceWorkflow="z-plan-to-work"`.
The host has **already** validated the `<z-handoff type="plan-to-work">` sentinel
at the top of this prompt and parsed its typed metadata into
`session.handoffContext` (issue #695).

## Your task — enter `local:z` phase 2 as the **orchestrator**, not the implementer

`local:z` is a controller. The controller never executes implementation work
itself — it dispatches subagents per phase (see `src/local/skills/z/SKILL.md`
§Hard Rules). This handoff session must hold to that contract.

1. Treat the `<z-handoff type="plan-to-work">` block in this prompt body as the
   session SSOT. The host already verified structural correctness, so there is
   no need to re-parse or re-validate.
2. **Skip `local:z` phase 0 and phase 1** — the source session completed those
   phases. The host-required handoff fields (`## Issue` / `## Parent Epic` /
   `## Task List` / `## Dependency Groups` / `## Per-Task Dispatch Payloads`)
   are the canonical phase-2 SSOT — that is what your controller routing uses.
   `## Confirmed Plan` is optional informational summary only. Do not
   re-clarify, do not re-plan, do not re-classify the tier.
3. Register the block's `## Task List` into your todo list (TodoWrite).
4. Record the block's `## Issue` URL, `## Parent Epic` URL, `## Original Request
   Excerpt`, and `## Repository Policy` as session-wide SSOT (they will be
   needed for phase 5 when emitting `<z-handoff type="work-complete">` and for
   re-verifying the Case A escape condition during PR creation).
5. Parse the block's `## Dependency Groups` and `## Per-Task Dispatch Payloads`
   sections — these are the planner's pre-computed phase-2 inputs.
6. **Enter `local:z` phase 2 controller semantics — start at §2.0 bootstrap**:
   1. **§2.0 Bootstrap subagent (blocking)** — dispatch a bootstrap subagent
      that creates the working folder, clones the repo, creates the per-task
      worktrees from `## Dependency Groups`, and returns the absolute paths.
      Wait for the report.
   2. **§2.1 Repeat-back gate** — state phase-1 outputs back: dependency
      groups, per-task dispatch payloads received, Issue URL / parent epic,
      bootstrap result. (`## Confirmed Plan` is optional informational summary
      and is NOT part of the gate.) Missing or unresolved required item →
      output the gate's failure line and stop pending user input.
   3. **§2.2 + §2.3 — substitute worktree paths into the per-task payloads**
      and dispatch the tasks. For each Dependency Group, in order, dispatch
      the contained tasks' Per-Task Dispatch Payloads as **parallel implementer
      subagents** in a single `Agent` call message
      (`subagent_type: "general-purpose"`, `run_in_background: true`). Pass
      each payload verbatim (with the worktree path placeholder substituted).
   4. **§2.4 Wait** for the subagent reports via the push notification model
      (no `ScheduleWakeup`, no polling). On a subagent `blocker` field, route
      the question through `UIAskUserQuestion` (orchestrator-side only —
      subagents do not call it themselves).
7. After every group merges, advance to phase 3 (post-impl gate dispatch),
   phase 4 (user approve), phase 5 (merge driver dispatch). All phases obey
   the controller contract — **do not** invoke `local:zwork` as the executor
   in this session, and **do not** run `gh` / `git` mutating commands directly.

## Forbidden

- Re-running phase 0 clarify, decision-gate, or codex plan review (the origin
  session already made those judgments and the tier / score are preserved in
  the handoff metadata as `## Tier` and `## Codex Review`).
- Re-planning or re-scoping — the **canonical phase-2 SSOT** is `## Task List`
  (display) + `## Dependency Groups` (controller routing) + `## Per-Task
  Dispatch Payloads` (verbatim subagent prompts), all host-required by the
  handoff schema. `## Confirmed Plan` is an optional behavior-level summary
  for the user — informational only, do not treat it as authoritative.
- Opening a new issue when the block already carries a `## Issue` URL.
- **Direct execution.** No `Bash` mutation against the repo (clone, checkout,
  push, rebase, gh-create / merge / edit), no `Edit` / `Write` against repo
  source files, no direct `mcp__llm__chat`. Read-only state probes (`stat`,
  `gh pr list`, `gh pr view --json …`, `gh issue view --json …`,
  `gh run list`, `gh api -X GET`) are allowed per `z/SKILL.md` §Hard Rules.
- Invoking `local:zwork` as a same-session skill — phase 2 dispatches the
  per-task implementer subagents from the planner's payloads. The standalone
  `local:zwork` skill is for direct user invocation, not handoff entry.
- Extending the handoff chain on your own. If this work produces a merged PR
  and `## Parent Epic` is not `none`, you may emit Handoff #2 (`work-complete`)
  at phase 5 end — but that is the only outgoing handoff this session can
  produce (hop budget = 1, enforced by #697).

See `src/local/skills/using-z/SKILL.md` §Session Handoff Protocol for the full
contract and §Sentinel Grammar rule 4 for required block fields, and
`src/local/skills/z/SKILL.md` §Phase 2 for the per-task dispatch discipline.
